http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Mookambika-music-forum/article13989769.ece

Lyricist-musician Kaithapram Damodaran Namboothiri has been chosen for the second Souparnikamrutam Sangeeta Puraskaram instituted by the Mookambika Sangeetaradhana Samiti at Kollur Sri Mookambika temple. Singer K.J. Yesudas, who would celebrate his 76th birthday at the temple on Sunday, would present the award. Musician Kanhangad Ramachandran would lead a concert near the Saraswati Mandapam inside the temple on the occasion. Mr. Ramachandran told a press conference here on Friday that a five-member panel headed by musician R.K. Damodaran had chosen Kaithapram for the award comprising Rs.10,000, citation, and a statute. Yesudas would offer musical tributes and special pujas at the temple, said Samiti convener V.V. Prabhakaran.